import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='longitude', y='latitude', hue='country', palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude across the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Country', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    country_counts = data['country'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=country_counts.index, y=country_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Airports')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports across different countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.legend(title='Countries', labels=country_counts.index, loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group by city and concatenate airport names
    grouped_data = data.groupby('city')['name'].apply(lambda x: ', '.join(x)).reset_index()

    # Create a text string of airport names for each city
    text = ' '.join(airport for airport in grouped_data['name'])

    # Generate a word cloud
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=800, background_color='white', colormap='viridis', max_words=150).generate(text)

    # Display the word cloud
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names across different cities?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group by country and concatenate airport names
    grouped_data = data.groupby('country')['name'].apply(lambda x: ', '.join(x)).reset_index()

    # Create a dictionary with country as key and concatenated airport names as value
    country_airport_names = dict(zip(grouped_data['country'], grouped_data['name']))

    # Generate word cloud
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white', colormap='viridis').generate_from_frequencies(country_airport_names)

    # Plot the word cloud
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 7))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('Word cloud of airport names in different countries', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
